snippet.textDisplay:
I left before this commercial aired during superbowl to go pickup pizzas. But I had my NFL app on because I wasn't about to miss any part of the game.
Then this commercial came on while I was driving. And I heard it. I was sobbing.
I came back and everyone was like "did they not have our order ready" lol
I was like "NO that google commercial" and everyone knew. Haha.

If you're ever lucky enough to have a Loretta or this guy, don't take it for granted. Cherish it. Nurture it.
I don't know alot about life, I just know that love like this is so rare. 💚💚

snippet.textDisplay: I seriously hate this ad. It leaves me sick inside ~ and no, it didn't make me cry, it makes me angry. It shows no respect for the reality of loss, grief, loneliness, and the prospect of spending the rest of your dwindling life so alone that the only 'friend' you have to share memories with is a soulless I.T. software package pretending to be a home care companion. Or for the hell of losing one's grip on memories, and having no loved ones to create any  further reality with. Damn Google for this. "Hey, Google - remember how Loretta died. Remember what she looked like in her coffin." Come ON! Loss and aging are not sweet little valentines. If you've lost someone you don't know how to live without, this ad is not touching, it's devastating.
